Notes: The screened strain HGUP191049 and the type of Ep. latusicollum are phylogenetically similar as they cluster together with well support (
Supplementary Figure 1
). Our collection resembles the type CGMCC 3.18346 in having a pycnidial wall, conidiogenous cells, and conidia. However, our collection slightly differs from the type in having aggregated conidiomata rather than solitary conidiomata (Chen et al., 2017). Therefore, the examined morphology overlaps and is phylogenetically identical to Ep. latusicollum. We report our collection as a new host record of Ep. latusicollum from the stem of R. roxburghii.

